# Docker build-context excludes.
#
# Docker only reads `.dockerignore` from the BUILD CONTEXT root, and our
# Dockerfile uses the parent directory (`arbitro-io/`) as context so it
# can also COPY the sibling `arbitro-kit/`. This file therefore lives in
# the repo for source-of-truth + reviewability, and gets staged at the
# real context root before `docker build`:
#
#   cp arbitro/.dockerignore .dockerignore
#   docker build -f arbitro/Dockerfile -t arbitro .
#
# CI runs that cp automatically (.github/workflows/ci.yml).

# Cargo build artifacts — gigabytes on a dev workstation, kill context
# transfer if not excluded. Fresh CI checkouts don't have these, but the
# rule still applies on cached runners.
**/target/

# Git history — `arbitro-kit/.git` clone alone is several MB. The image
# is statically linked from source; no git state is needed at build time.
**/.git/

# Docs and agent notes — not consumed by the build.
**/*.md
**/.agent/
**/.claude/

# Editor / OS / Node noise.
**/node_modules/
**/.idea/
**/.vscode/
**/.DS_Store

# Sibling repos that may share the parent dir on a dev machine but are
# not part of the broker build.
arbitro-ts/
arbitro-go-server/
arbitro-raft/
arbitro-baseline/
